# Two build families use the REPO ROOT as their Docker context:
#   - install-smoke clean rooms (install-smoke/*.Dockerfile) — need install-smoke/
#   - the dashboard image (frontend/Dockerfile) — needs the npm workspace
#     manifests + packages/ + frontend/ sources
# Everything else (the 5GB+ of backend/data/*.db, node_modules, .worktrees,
# build output, .git) would just bloat the context — and a live SQLite file
# mid-write even breaks the tar. Keep the context tiny + deterministic.
# marketing/ stays excluded: frontend/Dockerfile prunes missing workspaces, so
# the dev tree builds the same way the filtered public mirror does.
# A `.dockerignore` only applies at the CONTEXT root — per-directory copies
# would be inert — so this file is the single gate for root-context builds.
#
# Note: the backend image builds from `./backend` context (see docker-compose.yml),
# NOT the repo root, so this file does not affect it.
*
!install-smoke
!package.json
!package-lock.json
!packages
!frontend
**/node_modules
frontend/dist
frontend/.env*
